---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Noah Airmet, a software developer and cybersecurity student pursuing practical AI governance.">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <p class="indexed-label"><span>01</span> About</p>
    <h1>A builder learning to govern what gets built.</h1>
    <p>
      I’m Noah Airmet, a junior developer at Simplicity Group and a cybersecurity
      student at Brigham Young University. I’m pursuing AI governance and GRC
      because I want policy to remain connected to the systems, incentives, and
      everyday decisions it is meant to shape.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="page-content">
    <section class="prose-grid">
      <h2>Current work</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>I develop Laravel and Angular features for regulated insurance software, including API integrations and workflows that handle non-public personal information.</p>
        <p>Working inside that environment makes governance questions concrete: which data can enter an AI tool, where authorization belongs, how input is validated, what a vendor retains, and who reviews the result before it matters.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose-grid" id="principles">
      <h2>Operating principles</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <h3>Protect people and entrusted data.</h3>
        <p>Security and privacy are not paperwork around the work. They are part of why the work deserves trust.</p>
        <h3>Keep responsibility legible.</h3>
        <p>AI can assist a decision or accelerate an implementation. A person and an institution still need to remain answerable for what happens.</p>
        <h3>Build controls that survive real workflows.</h3>
        <p>A control that collapses under deadline pressure was never fully implemented. Good governance has to understand the people and systems expected to carry it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="prose-grid">
      <h2>Background</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Before software development, I supported Apple and Windows devices, inventory, purchasing, and distributed technology operations. I also led volunteer teams in Mexico City and work professionally in Spanish.</p>
        <p>Across those settings, the recurring problem has been translation: turning technical constraints into decisions people can understand and follow.</p>
        <div class="resume-actions">
          <a class="solid-link" href="/resume/">Read résumé</a>
          <a class="underlined-link" href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>Contact me →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
